quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,113,"They are not all alike. Of the people of the Book there is an upright community, reciting the revelations of Allah throughout the night, falling prostrate (in Surrender)"
  3,114,"They believe in Allah, and in the last day, and bid intelligent (or right) conduct, and forbid what is stupid (or wrong), and vie with one another in good works; these are among the righteous"
  3,115,"What good they do, surely Allah will not deny its merit, for Allah is Aware of those who fear (or repel) evil"
  3,116,"Verily, those who disbelieve, their wealth and children are of no service to them against Allah; they are the rightful owners of the Fire, and they shall dwell therein"
  3,117,"The likeness of what they spend in this life of the world is as the likeness of wind wherein is a cold blast that falls upon the harvest of a people who have wronged themselves and destroys it. It is not Allah who wrongs them, but it is themselves they wr"
  3,118,"O you who believe! Take not for intimates others than your own folk, who would not fail to ruin you; they love to obstruct you. Hatred is shown by their mouths; but what their breasts conceal is greater still. We have made manifest to you Our revelations"
  3,119,"Verily, it is you who love them, but they love not you; and you believe in the whole of the Scripture. But when they meet you they say, \"We believe;\" and when they go aside they bite their fingertips at you through rage. Say, \"Die in your r"
  3,120,"If good luck touches you it is bad for them, but if bad luck befalls you they rejoice therein; yet if you are patient and fear, their tricks shall not harm you. Lo, Allah is surrounding what they do"
  3,121,"When you did set forth early from your household to settle for the believers the positions for battle, Allah was Hearer and Knower"
  3,122,"When two companies of you almost fell away in cowardice but Allah was their Guardian (or Protecting Friend), for on Allah surely do believers put their trust"
  3,123,Allah gave you victory at Badr when you were in a contemptible force; so do your duty to Allah in thankfulness
  3,124,"When you did say unto the believers, \"Is it not enough for you that your Lord supports you with three thousand of the angels sent down from on high"
  3,125,"Yea, if you persevere and avoid evil, and the enemy attacks you suddenly, your Lord will assist you with five thousand of His angels with force"
  3,126,"Allah ordained this only as glad tidings to comfort your heart withal, for victory comes but from Allah, the Mighty, the Wise"
  3,127,"That He may cut off some of the faithless, or overwhelm them that they may retire frustrated (from their purpose)"
  3,128,"It (the concern, responsibility or decision) is not for you whether He turns towards them again or punish them; for, verily, they are evil-doers"
  3,129,"To Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and in the earth. He forgives whom He will, and punishes whom He will. Allah is Forgiving and Merciful"
  3,130,"O you who believe! Devour not usury doubling and redoubling, but do your duty to Allah that you may be successful"
  3,131,Avoid the fire which is prepared for the faithless
  3,132,"And obey Allah and His Messenger, that you may get mercy"